Field Documentation

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::classification

Classification tag information from the HiGig device FFP.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::dp

Drop Precedence indicates the traffic rate violation status of the packet measured by the ingress module.

  • 00: GREEN
  • 01: RED
  • 10: Reserved
  • 11: Yellow
uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::dst_modid_mgid

When MCST=0, this field indicates the destination XGS module to which the packet will be delivered.

When MCST=1, this field indicates higher order bits of the Multicast Group ID.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::dst_pid_mgid

When MCST=0, this field indicates a port associated with the module indicated by the DST_MODID, through which the packet will exit the system.

When MCST=1, this field indicates lower order bits of the Multicast Group ID

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::dst_t

Destination Trunk: Indicates that the destination port is a member of a trunk group.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::dst_tgid

Destination Trunk Group ID: Trunk group ID of the destination port.

The DO_NOT_LEARN bit is overlaid on the second bit of this field.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::hdr_ext_len

This field is valid only if the HGI field is a b'10' and it indicates the extension to the standard 12-bytes of XGS HiGig header.

Each unit represents 4 bytes, giving a total of 16 additional extension bytes. Value of b'101', b'110' and b'111' are reserved. For HGI field value of b'01' this field should be b'01'. For all other values of HGI it is don't care.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::ingress_tagged

Ingress Tagged: Indicates whether the packet was tagged when it originally ingressed the system.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::k_sop

The delimiter indicating the start of a packet transmission.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::l3

L3: Indicates that the packet is L3 switched.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::label_present

Label Present: Indicates that header contains a 20-bit VC label: HiGig+ added field.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::lbid

Load Balancing ID indicates a packet flow hashing index computed by the ingress XGS module for statistical distribution of packet flows through a multipath fabric.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::mcst

MCST indicates whether the packet should be unicast or multicast forwarded through the XGS switching fabric

  • 0: Unicast
  • 1: Mulitcast.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::mirror

Mirror: XGS3 mode: a mirror copy packet.

XGS1/2 mode: Indicates that the packet was switched and only needs to be mirrored.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::mirror_done

Mirroring Done: XGS1/2 mode: Indicates that the packet was mirrored and may still need to be switched.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::mirror_only

Mirror Only: XGS 1/2 mode: Indicates that the packet was switched and only needs to be mirrored.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::opcode

XGS HiGig op-code, indicating the type of packet 000 = Control frames used for CPU to CPU communications 001 = Unicast packet with destination resolved; The packet can be either Layer 2 unicast packet or L3 unicast packet that was routed in the ingress chip.

010 = Broadcast or unknown Unicast packet or unknown multicast, destined to all members of the VLAN 011 = L2 Multicast packet, destined to all ports of the group indicated in the L2MC_INDEX which is overlayed on DST_PORT/DST_MODID fields 100 = IP Multicast packet, destined to all ports of the group indicated in the IPMC_INDEX which is overlayed on DST_PORT/DST_MODID fields 101 = Reserved 110 = Reserved 111 = Reserved

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::pfm

Three Port Filtering Modes (0, 1, 2) used in handling registed/unregistered multicast (unknown L2 multicast and IPMC) packets.

This field is used when OPCODE is 011 or 100 Semantics of PFM bits are as follows; For registered L2 multicast packets: PFM= 0 ­ Flood to VLAN PFM= 1 or 2 ­ Send to group members in the L2MC table For unregistered L2 multicast packets: PFM= 0 or 1 ­ Flood to VLAN PFM= 2 ­ Drop the packet

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::ppd_type

Packet Processing Descriptor Type

  • 000: PPD Overlay1
  • 001: PPD Overlay2
  • 010~111: Reserved.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::src_modid

Source Module ID indicates the source XGS module from which the packet is originated.

(It can also be used for the fabric multicast load balancing purpose.)

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::src_pid

Source Port ID indicates a port associated with the module indicated by the SRC_MODID, through which the packet has entered the system.

uint32_t cvmx_higig2_header_t::src_t

If the MSB of this field is set, then it indicates the LAG the packet ingressed on, else it represents the physical port the packet ingressed on.

Traffic Class [3:0] indicates the distinctive Quality of Service (QoS) the switching fabric will provide when forwarding the packet through the fabric.
